modules.description: This module implements a GraphQL client for handling subscriptions, queries, and WebSocket control messages like ping and pong. It works with GraphQL operations defined by the `Q` module, using variables and response types specific to the query schema. Concrete use cases include subscribing to real-time updates, sending one-time queries, and managing WebSocket keep-alive signals.

Implements a GraphQL client for subscriptions, queries, and WebSocket control messages like ping/pong. Works with GraphQL operations defined by the `Q` module, using variables and response types specific to the query schema. Concrete use cases include subscribing to real-time updates, sending one-time queries, and managing WebSocket keep-alive signals.

This module defines the interface for executing GraphQL queries and handling their responses. It works with GraphQL operation definitions and JSON data structures to send requests and decode results. Concrete use cases include fetching data from a GraphQL API, handling query variables, and parsing typed responses using `graphql_ppx`-generated code.

This module implements a GraphQL client for executing queries, handling subscriptions, and managing WebSocket communication. It works with GraphQL operation definitions, query variables, and typed JSON responses, particularly integrating with `graphql_ppx`-generated code. Concrete use cases include fetching typed data from a GraphQL API, subscribing to real-time updates over WebSockets, and handling keep-alive signals during long-lived connections.
